ck</span>(<span style="color: #569cd6;">function</span>() { &nbsp;</div><br><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <span style="color: #9cdcfe;">location</span>.<span style="color: #dcdcaa;">reload</span>(<span style="color: #569cd6;">true</span>);</div><br><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; });</div><br><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; });</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; <span style="color: #808080;">&lt;/</span><span style="color: #569cd6;">script</span><span style="color: #808080;">&gt;</span></div><br><div><span style="color: #808080;">&lt;/</span><span style="color: #569cd6;">body</span><span style="color: #808080;">&gt;</span></div><div><span style="color: #808080;">&lt;/</span><span style="color: #569cd6;">html</span><span style="color: #808080;">&gt;</span></div></div><p><br></p><p>In the second example, We are using the <b>SetInterval() method</b> to call the .reload() function using jquery.</p><p>How to reload page after some time in jQuery<br></p><div class="alert funda-bg" style="color: rgb(212, 212, 212); background-color: rgb(30, 30, 30); font-family: Consolas, &quot;Courier New&quot;, monospace; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19px; white-space: pre;"><div><span style="color: #808080;">&lt;!</span><span style="color: #569cd6;">DOCTYPE</span> <span style="color: #9cdcfe;">html</span><span style="color: #808080;">&gt;</span></div><div><span style="color: #808080;">&lt;</span><span style="color: #569cd6;">html</span> <span style="color: #9cdcfe;">lang</span>=<span style="color: #ce9178;">"en"</span><span style="color: #808080;">&gt;</span></div><div><span style="color: #808080;">&lt;</span><span style="color: #569cd6;">head</span><span style="color: #808080;">&gt;</span></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; <span style="color: #808080;">&lt;</span><span style="color: #569cd6;">title</span><span style="color: #808080;">&gt;</span>Refresh or Reload a Page Using jQuery<span style="color: #808080;">&lt;/</span><span style="color: #569cd6;">title</